summarization.results: Music plays a vital role in expressing spirituality and connecting with God, as seen through the significance of singing and praying with Psalms in Christian tradition. Gregorian chant, originating in the 7th and 8th centuries, remains a cornerstone of Western sacred music, continuing to hold a significant place in Catholic culture and tradition. The enduring practice of chanting, rooted in monastic traditions, is still observed today, highlighting its ongoing relevance in the Church.
